From: "Christopher L. Crutchfield" <ccrutchf@ucsd.edu>
Date: Sun, 3 May 2026 10:51:33 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 7/7] =?UTF-8?q?ufs/phy:=20gs201=20=E2=80=94=20silence=20de?=
 =?UTF-8?q?bug=20instrumentation=20(dev=5Finfo=20->=20dev=5Fdbg)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The bring-up instrumentation we added while chasing the dl_err
0x80000002 wedge and the post-CDR-lock READ_10 tag-6 timeout has
become pure UART noise now that root causes are fixed. Each boot
emits ~7000 ufs-cmd-issue lines and dozens of CMU/UFSP/sysreg dumps,
totalling ~700 KB of console output — at 115200 baud that's ~70 s
of UART throttle alone, masking the real boot speed and keeping the
kmscon login prompt off-screen. AOSP avoids this with loglevel=4 and
by simply not having the prints; mainline upstream samsung-ufs is
also nowhere near this verbose.

Bulk convert all dev_info to dev_dbg in three files:

  drivers/ufs/core/ufshcd.c       per-SCSI-submission trace
  drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c   CMU/UFSP/sysreg dumps + h-stage tags
                                  + SMC_CMD_FMP_SECURITY/SMU return values
  drivers/phy/samsung/phy-gs101-ufs.c   cdr-instr lock-acquisition trace

dev_warn / dev_err for actual error paths are unchanged. Re-enable
selectively at runtime with `dyndbg=` on the kernel cmdline or
/sys/kernel/debug/dynamic_debug/control.

This is a quick "shut it up" pass — proper upstream-quality cleanup
(deleting the dump helpers outright, gating the rest behind a Kconfig
debug option) is owed before the felix patches go to lkml. Tracked in
the upstream-patches/ TODO and the auto-memory feedback_uart_verbosity
note.
